Interface TreeDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the vertex type of the graph
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.concurrent.Callable<TreeDecomposition<T>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BranchAndBoundDecomposer, BruteForceEliminationOrderDecomposer, CatchAndGlue, CopsAndRobber, DynamicProgrammingDecomposer, EliminationOrderDecomposer, ExactDecomposer, GraphSplitter, GreedyPathDecomposer, GreedyPermutationDecomposer, LimitedGraphSearch, LocalSearchDecomposer, MaximumCardinalitySearchDecomposer, RobertsonSeymourDecomposer, SATDecomposer, StochasticGreedyPermutationDecomposer

    public interface TreeDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.util.concurrent.Callable<TreeDecomposition<T>>
    The TreeDecomposer Interface describes a class that models an algorithm for computing a tree-decomposition. By implementing this interface, a class has to implement the Callable interface, which computes a tree-decomposition of vertex type T and G from a graph of vertex type G.

        TreeDecomposition<T> call()
                   throws java.lang.Exception
        This calls the execution of the tree-decomposition algorithm and returns the decomposition. The function is allowed to throw exceptions (as defined in the Callable interface), however, this should be specified more precisely.

      • getCurrentSolution

        TreeDecomposition<T> getCurrentSolution()
        This method returns the best solution found so far. This method should return null if @see call() was not called, or the algorithm does not found a solution yet, or if the algorithm is not anytime.
        Returns:
        the current best solution
